<br>
As for Iraq, I am not certain myself. But lets be clear here, Saddam is a ruthless killer. The guy was an assassian for chirstsake at one point. He is clearly building an arsenal of weapons of mass destruction, has thumbed his nose at the UN and gotten away with it, and opresses and gases his own people.<br>
<br>
As an budding engineer, I am learning that preventing a problem is much better then solving one after it starts. For example, how many lives might have been saved if we had gone into Afghanistan before the WTC attack and tore up the camps. We knew there were camps there, we know Al Qaeda was commited to harming and attacking the US, but it took the WTC crumbling before our eyes before we took the needed action. How many lives would have been spared if we had just gone after those bastards to begin with?<br>
<br>
Course, the problem is its hard sometimes to get people to spend money, (or in this case lives) to prevent problems. Cause you just don't know. We couldn't have known that by erasing Al Qaeda a few years ago we would could have saved the lives of hundreds of people. I guarentee if a nuke went off somewhere in the US made from a weapons program in Iraq, or some biological weapons unleashed, people would be saying, &quot;Why didn't we get rid of him before this happened?&quot; Hell even if Saddam doesn't use them himself, whats to prevent him from selling Antrax or smallpox to people like Al Qaeda? <br>
<br>
There is much more money to be made by opening up Iraqi oil then by going to war with Iraq. I think President Bush may have some ulterior motives, but they are probably personal rather then finanicial. Keep in mind, Saddam tried to assassanite Bush 1.0 not long after he left office. Thats W's own papa. <br>
<br>
I am kind of leary of running off to Iraq with Al Qaeda still at large. But then again, the Al Qaeda war is more of a shadow war, fought with satellites, spys, and special forces. Iraq is a target we can use all those nice toys we developed for a Soviet showdown that never occured. So perhaps we can take on both at once.<br>
<br>
Going to war is not something to be regarded lightly, or casually. But taking out Saddam now might prevent a great tradegy in the future. We won't know if we do it of course, but we will know if we wake up to find New York in a mushroom cloud.<br>
<br>
As for the UN, it as proven a largely ineffective and useless organization. I see Bush made an effort to get them on his side, but really, everyone knows the UN is a joke unless the US is backing them up. They are good for getting good guy points for your side, but you dont need them and really, all having UN support does is make it look more official and legal when the US military goes in and does what needs to be done. <p><img src=http://mywebpages.comcast.net/pbakas/mikel_sig2.jpg><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=67382>See if your stuff is better then mine</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub141.ezboard.com/umikelmorbidus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mikel Morbidus</A> at: 10/13/02 12:04:35 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#77839D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub141.ezboard.com/uapollohades.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Apollohades</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator <br> Yummy Erudite</span><br>  Posts: 1473<br> <font color=#F7E5C3>(10/12/02 10:11:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub141.ezboard.com/feverquestpeoplefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=519.topic&index=39>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: war soon?</span><hr size=1> *blink*<br>
